---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import Button from '../../components/Button.astro';
import SectionLabel from '../../components/SectionLabel.astro';
import MetricBox from '../../components/MetricBox.astro';
import { BOOKING_URL } from '../../config';
---

<Base
  title="Incosmetics Global: Lead Capture Strategy — Allenby Advisory"
  description="How a new NFC-based content capture technology multiplied leads and created a new exhibitor revenue stream at Incosmetics Global."
>
  <Nav />

  <main>

    <!-- PAGE HEADER -->
    <section class="page-header">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <p class="breadcrumb"><a href="/client-successes">← Client successes</a></p>
        <SectionLabel text="Case study — project delivery" />
        <h1 class="page-h1">Incosmetics Global: Lead Capture Strategy</h1>
        <p class="page-intro">How a new NFC-based content capture technology multiplied leads and created a new exhibitor revenue stream at one of Europe's leading cosmetics ingredients events.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TOP SECTION -->
    <section class="case-top reveal">
      <div class="case-top-inner">
        <div class="case-text">
          <p class="case-label">The project in brief</p>
          <h2 class="case-h2">From Feature-Zone Experiment to Show-Wide Digital Lead Capture</h2>
          <p class="case-intro">The event had an existing self-scan product limited to feature zones. Ade identified an opportunity to scale it show-wide using NFC badging technology — turning a niche feature into a commercially significant, opt-out exhibitor product.</p>
          <Button label="Get in touch about a similar project" href="/book" />
        </div>
        <div class="meta-card">
          <div class="meta-items">
            <div class="meta-item">
              <span class="meta-label">Event</span>
              <span class="meta-value">Incosmetics Global</span>
            </div>
            <div class="meta-item">
              <span class="meta-label">Locations</span>
              <span class="meta-value">Paris / Barcelona (alternating)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="meta-item">
              <span class="meta-label">Service type</span>
              <span class="meta-value">Project delivery</span>
            </div>
            <div class="meta-item">
              <span class="meta-label">Technology</span>
              <span class="meta-value">NFC badge scanning</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <MetricBox number="4×" description="Increase in paying exhibitors" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- BODY COLUMNS -->
    <section class="case-body">
      <div class="grid-separator body-grid">
        <div class="body-col reveal">
          <p class="col-header">The challenge</p>
          <p>The event had a content capture solution limited to feature zones. The brief was to review the existing strategy and implement a show-wide approach that would scale — increasing both exhibitor and visitor engagement with digital lead capture.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="body-col reveal">
          <p class="col-header">What Ade did</p>
          <p>Devised a value proposition and technology implementation strategy around NFC badging devices. When a visitor taps the device, their badge ID is captured — triggering an automatic daily "trip report" of everything they collected, with no manual data work required for exhibitors.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="body-col reveal">
          <p class="col-header">The results</p>
          <p>Leads captured multiplied significantly. The proportion of exhibitors paying for the product increased fourfold — to over 90% — in the year following the initial trial. A new exhibitor revenue stream was created from a product previously offered for free.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- NARRATIVE SECTION -->
    <section class="narrative-section reveal">
      <div class="narrative-inner">
        <h3 class="narrative-h3">The Full Story</h3>
        <p>Incosmetics Global is the premier trade event for cosmetics ingredients, alternating between Paris and Barcelona. Exhibitors use it to demonstrate new innovations and discuss supply for the coming year — a commercially high-stakes environment where lead quality and follow-up matter significantly.</p>
        <p>The event already had a self-scan product attached to its feature zones — curated showcase areas designed to drive exhibitor footfall. Small badge-scanning devices allowed visitors to self-scan and receive content post-event. The opportunity was to take that concept and scale it across the entire show floor using a more capable technology.</p>
        <p>Working with the Global Innovation Team and the UK Digital Team, Ade trialled NFC-enabled devices that allow visitors to tap their badge at any exhibitor stand. The tap triggers a capture — no action required from the exhibitor — and at the end of each day, visitors receive an automatic "trip report" containing everything they collected: company descriptions, product information, brochures and contact details.</p>
        <p>The implementation required simultaneous process changes across several areas: an NFC pairing step added to badge collection, an exhibitor onboarding communications programme (pre-event and onsite), and clear onsite guidance for exhibitors on device placement for best results.</p>
        <p>Critically, the value proposition was reframed. Rather than being sold as a paid-for lead retrieval add-on, the product was redesigned as an opt-out feature — built on the idea of enabling visitors to collect digital content from anywhere at the event without carrying paper brochures. The product was offered free of charge in year one to prove value, then introduced as a standard contract item in subsequent years.</p>
        <p>The Global Innovation Team collaborated closely with the vendor to analyse the rich dataset generated from the show floor — delivering exhibitor-facing insights that reinforced the product's value and gave sales and marketing teams new intelligence about how visitors engaged with the event.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- OUTCOMES SECTION -->
    <section class="outcomes-section">
      <div class="outcomes-inner">
        <h3 class="outcomes-h3">Headline Outcomes</h3>
        <div class="grid-separator outcomes-grid reveal">
          <div class="outcome-cell">
            <span class="outcome-number">4×</span>
            <span class="outcome-desc">Increase in paying exhibitors</span>
          </div>
          <div class="outcome-cell">
            <span class="outcome-number">90%+</span>
            <span class="outcome-desc">Exhibitor uptake in year two</span>
          </div>
          <div class="outcome-cell">
            <span class="outcome-number">New</span>
            <span class="outcome-desc">Revenue stream created</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ROLE STRIP -->
    <section class="role-strip reveal">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <p class="role-text"><span class="role-label">Ade's role:</span> Product strategy, implementation strategy, customer communication strategy, metrics and reporting, and supporting the team through end-to-end delivery.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FOOTER CTA -->
    <div class="dark-section">
      <div class="cta-inner">
        <h2>Working on Something Similar?</h2>
        <p>Whether you're looking to improve exhibitor lead capture, launch a digital content strategy, or scale an existing product — Ade would welcome the conversation.</p>
        <div style="margin-top: 32px;">
          <Button label="Book a free 30-minute call" href="/book" variant="light" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  /* Page header */
  .page-header { background: var(--offwhite); }

  .breadcrumb {
    font-family: 'Archivo', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.10em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--midgrey);
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .page-h1 {
    font-family: 'Archivo Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 52px;
    line-height: 1.06;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .page-intro {
    max-width: 600px;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--body);
  }

  /* Top section */
  .case-top { background: var(--white); }

  .case-top-inner {
    max-width: 1280px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-2xl) var(--space-lg);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 240px;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .case-label {
    font-family: 'Archivo', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.10em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--midgrey);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .case-h2 {
    font-family: 'Archivo Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 34px;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    max-width: 540px;
  }

  .case-intro {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--body);
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    max-width: 520px;
  }

  /* Meta card */
  .meta-card {
    background: var(--offwhite);
    border: 0.5px solid var(--lightgrey);
    padding: 22px;
  }

  .meta-items { margin-bottom: 16px; }

  .meta-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding: 8px 0;
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--lightgrey);
  }

  .meta-label {
    font-family: 'Archivo', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.10em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--midgrey);
    margin-bottom: 2px;
  }

  .meta-value {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* Body columns */
  .case-body { background: var(--offwhite); }

  .body-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    max-width: 1280px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .body-col {
    padding: var(--space-lg) 28px;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--body);
  }

  .col-header {
    font-family: 'Archivo', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.10em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--midgrey);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  /* Narrative section */
  .narrative-section {
    background: var(--offwhite);
    padding: var(--space-2xl) var(--space-lg);
    border-top: 0.5px solid var(--lightgrey);
  }

  .narrative-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .narrative-h3 {
    font-family: 'Archivo Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 22px;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .narrative-section p {
    font-family: 'Archivo', sans-serif;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--body);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  /* Outcomes section */
  .outcomes-section {
    background: var(--white);
    padding: var(--space-2xl) var(--space-lg);
    border-top: 0.5px solid var(--lightgrey);
  }

  .outcomes-inner {
    max-width: 1280px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .outcomes-h3 {
    font-family: 'Archivo Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 22px;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .outcomes-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  }

  .outcome-cell {
    background: var(--charcoal);
    padding: 20px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .outcome-number {
    font-family: 'Archivo Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 32px;
    color: var(--white);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  .outcome-desc {
    font-family: 'Archivo', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.10em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #888780;
  }

  /* Role strip */
  .role-strip {
    background: var(--white);
    border-top: 0.5px solid var(--lightgrey);
    padding: 24px 40px;
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--lightgrey);
  }

  .role-text {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--body);
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .role-label {
    font-family: 'Archivo', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* Footer CTA */
  .dark-section { padding: var(--space-2xl) 0; }

  .cta-inner {
    max-width: 1280px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--space-lg);
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-h1 { font-size: 34px; }
    .case-top-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .body-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .outcomes-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .role-strip { padding: 24px 20px; }
    .narrative-section { padding: var(--space-2xl) 20px; }
    .outcomes-section { padding: var(--space-2xl) 20px; }
  }
</style>
